Change locks to all doors. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4c/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4c/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Make sure the windows and other entries are locked from the inside. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d8/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d8/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

This will keep the property from becoming an eyesore or a dumping ground in the neighborhood. Mow the lawn. Remember to check back every week or two to keep it mowed. Trim hedges, bushes, trees and weeds. You do not have to do extensive yard and landscaping work when cleaning the home, but make sure it looks neat. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c1/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/c1/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Tow any junk cars that are in the driveway or on the property and haul away any trash or debris that has gathered outside the house. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1c/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1c/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Drain any swimming pools and secure any outbuildings including sheds, barns or storage buildings. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1c/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1c/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

The lender will want real estate agents to be able to show the property, so it must be in presentable condition. Haul away any trash and broken or damaged appliances, furniture and other items left in the home. You might want to try selling or auctioning anything that was left behind and is still of value. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3b/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3b/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Vacuum, sweep and mop the floors. Remove any stained or damaged carpets and fix or replace broken tiles, light fixtures and hardware. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e1/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e1/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Wipe down walls, surfaces and other fixtures with an antibacterial spray or cloth. Note any major damage so the lender can decide whether to make any repairs. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d9/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d9/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Once the water is shut off, there will still be water left in the pipes. If that water is left in there, it can freeze and damage the home's plumbing. Turn on every faucet and water fixture once the main water is turned off to drain. Flush toilets until they will not flush again. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/02/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/02/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":315,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":520.934065934066,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Hook up an air compressor to a ice maker supply line to blow out any remaining water in the pipes. Remember to turn faucets back off after you drain the water. Otherwise, the house could flood once the water is turned back on. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7f/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7f/Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Clean-and-Winterize-Repossessed-Homes-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":315,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":520.934065934066,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
